{
  "stem": "1216.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "But I remember getting-- every afternoon-- a piece of bread with probably margarine on it and some sugar.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "I took that piece of bread, and there was a tree with very low branches.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And I climbed that tree and ate my bread in peace and quiet, because nobody knew I was up there, so nobody could steal it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And once I'd eaten it, of course, it was safe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "We stayed there for about a week.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "We were allowed to go into town.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "We didn't all that much, partly because we were probably too weak, and partly because the inhabitants of the town did give us rather odd looks.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And then after that week was over, again, somehow, we went to a field-- literally a field-- a meadow.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And everybody stood there looking at the sky.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there were some other children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a Professor Myers, a friend of my father's, a Dutchman, and he had his daughter with him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And two of us were looking at each other, kind of going, what is all this?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, looking at the sky.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There wasn't anything there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it turned out that a plane came.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had never seen a plane, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That turned out to be an army transport plane.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that took us back to Holland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, a number of the Dutch had already left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was the last group, and my parents and I went back to Holland, and we were flown to Eindhoven, famous for the Philips Electronics factories, then and now.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was, in fact, in those factories that we were quartered, because they were empty at the time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And once again, a big room, no beds, good mattresses though, but on the floor.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
